    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Personnel evacuated platform to supporting derrick barge",
      "Onsite supervisor assessed situation and began mitigation",
      "Casing valves tested for combustible gas at wellhead",
      "3/8 inch pilot hole drilled through casings",
      "Compressed air supplied to casings and circulated through annulus",
      "Multiple combustible gas tests conducted",
      "Site deemed safe and operations resumed"
    ],
    "summary": "On October 2, 2015, at approximately 20:25 hours, a flash fire occurred during decommissioning activities on Matagorda Island 685, Platform A, OCS-G-04548. Tetra Offshore welding personnel were cutting slots in the B-1 conductor for installation of lifting plates when an Oxylance burning bar ignited flammable gas trapped inside the 13 3/8 inch x 9 5/8 inch casing annulus at the plus ten deck. Initial combustible gas checks at the cellar deck level and wellhead detected 0% LEL, but failed to detect trapped gas in the annulus. The flash fire burned for approximately 30 seconds before self-extinguishing. No injuries, pollution, or property damage were reported.",
    "recommendations": [
      "All decommissioning activities involving cutting of tubing and/or casing with hot work should require testing and verification that tubing/casing are inert and free of flammable substances",
      "May include circulation with inert fluid, venting, and/or creating access for purging to ensure comprehensive combustible gas testing where routine monitoring cannot detect trapped combustible gas",
      "Reference Safety Alert Notice Number 153 (February 12, 1988): cutting tubing during removal with torch does not conform to safe and workmanlike practices"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "flash fire",
      "trapped flammable gas",
      "casing annulus",
      "Oxylance burning bar",
      "combustible gas detection",
      "hot work permit",
      "decommissioning",
      "gas migration"
    ]
  },
